-- India Proposes Bartering Wheat for Oil From Iran, Times Says
-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 2012-02-09T03:36:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/india-proposes-bartering-wheat-for-oil-from-iran-times-says.html
India ’s external affairs ministry has
proposed paying for Iranian crude imports with wheat exports to
the Persian Gulf nation, the  Economic Times  reported, citing an
unidentified person with knowledge of the development.  No such proposal has been received by the food ministry,
Food Minister K.V. Thomas told the newspaper.  The two countries are seeking a solution for payment for
India’s crude oil imports from the Islamic Republic amid
escalating economic and financial sanctions against  Iran .  To contact the reporter on this story:
